-- Deals of the day- Mergers and acquisitions
-- 
-- Wed Jan 15, 2014 06:43AM EST
-- None



Jan 15 (Reuters) - The following bids, mergers, acquisitions and disposals were reported by 1130 GMT on Wednesday:

** Chilean energy company Enersis SA <ENE.SN> plans to offer to buy the shares of its Brazilian unit, Companhia Energetica do Ceara <COCE5.SA>, it does not already own in a deal it said would be worth around $645 million. [ID:nL2N0KP01J]   ** China's Tencent Holdings Ltd <0700.HK> said it will invest HK$1.5 billion ($193.45 million) in logistics and warehouse firm China South City Holdings Ltd <1668.HK> to develop its e-commerce and logistics business. [ID:nB9N0K200Q]  ** Forbes Media, the company known for its namesake magazine and ranking the world's richest people, has caught the attention of six different companies including Germany's Axel Springer AG <SPRGn.DE>, according to a report in the Wall Street Journal. [ID:nL2N0KO28O]  ** Bharti Airtel Ltd <BRTI.NS> and Vodafone Group Plc's <VOD.L> Indian unit submitted applications to bid in a spectrum auction next month, separate sources at the two companies said. [ID:nD8N0KN009]  ** The Chinese private equity firm Hony Capital is examining a bid for Britain's United Biscuits Holdings Ltd and may be teaming up with a corporate buyer, Bloomberg reported. [ID:nL3N0KP27V]